Description: Foot sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery kylix type C or stemless cup; straight profile; glazed save for stand surface and narrow band at top of iutside of foot; added red band on upper surface at junction with stem; ‘E’ incised on inner face of foot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 521)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1471)
